cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software or its associated formal specification, please cite it as below."
title: "Machine-checkable compliance for AGI Governance: Reference implementation and LegalRuleML specification"
type: software
version: "1.3"
date-released: "2026-07-01"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/pcoronaf/agi-governance"
url: "https://w3id.org/agi-governance"
abstract: >-
  Reference implementation and formal specification for a machine-checkable
  AGI governance compliance model.  Includes a LegalRuleML-compatible norm
  encoding extended with an AGI Evidence Vocabulary (agiev), a Python-based
  compliance engine, synthetic evidence bundles for three case-study domains,
  and a validation runner.  Engine v1.1 added a corrected evaluation precondition (mandatory
  null/absent-field checking before threshold evaluation; paper Section 8.3).
  v1.2 added type-and-range guards, per-norm fault isolation, and absent-
  confidence handling; v1.3 enforces lifecycle-stage scoping and provenance
  presence. A blind conformance evaluation by three independent LLMs (paper
  Section 8.4) is included under conformance/.
